    <title>Flat Hunt Developer Guide</title>
    <para>
        <libraryname>TRAFFIC</libraryname> [<link linkend="references">sa05</link>],
            <projectname>Touch</projectname> [<link linkend="references">rk05</link>] and
            <projectname>Flat Hunt</projectname> is software that hopefully makes learning to
        program more fun and more interesting for you. <libraryname>TRAFFIC</libraryname> is a
        library that supports the reading and display of public transportation systems. A library is
        a piece of software whose functionality can be used by other software. <projectname>Flat
            Hunt</projectname> is an application that uses the <libraryname>TRAFFIC</libraryname>
        library to model a city map. For the visualization the
        <libraryname>EiffelMedia</libraryname> Library (formerly known as
        <libraryname>ESDL</libraryname> [<link linkend="references">tgb03, bb04</link>]) is used. It is a strategy game, similar to Scotland Yard,
        but with a different background story (for more information about the story and gameplay of
            <projectname>Flat Hunt</projectname>, see <link linkend="../user_guide/index">Flat Hunt
            User Guide</link>). <projectname>Touch</projectname> is also an application that uses
        the <libraryname>TRAFFIC</libraryname> library. For more information to
        <libraryname>TRAFFIC</libraryname> and <projectname>Touch</projectname>: see [<link
            linkend="references">sa05</link>] and [<link linkend="references">rk05</link>] or visit
            <ulink url="http://se.inf.ethz.ch/traffic">this website</ulink>. </para>
